Amazing!  You have just reinvented Keynes, which is a step forward over
some of the gung-ho I've-got-mine-fuck-you-Jack rhetoric on this list.  I
find it interesting that as crony capitalist Asia melts down and parts of
eternally-in-hock Latin America are blown away, some views are shifting
back toward a kind of Keynesian revival.

One prudential motive for adopting the views typically favoured in Europe,
Oz, etc (and of course large sections of the USA) is caught quite aptly by
