I have to disagree here.  I don't think an infant needs to process input in a
*rational* format in order to be aware of it - think of all the irrational people
out there! :-).  All healthy infants respond to environmental stimuli immediately
after birth.  I would call that response awareness.  Proving they are self-aware
however, may prove as difficult as doing it for anyone else.

