aware that their are many alternative 'realities' to that of crime and
struggle.  As of 1977, 67 of the initial 80 had been released, with only
2 ever going back to prison.  Lets see, 2 out of 67 gives us ~3%
recidivism.  I'd say that was a pretty darn good success rate for only
*one* study!

